{
  "stem": "10829.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] They shot him and said, this is what we're going to do [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to anybody who doesn't listen.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or we're going to do-- so we are in charge, and you do what we tell you, unless you end up like this.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, we couldn't touch him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was laying right down there in his blood.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We couldn't touch him like that for days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was-- that was-- the rabbi-- the rabbi in-- in those days, I-- I don't know if-- most-- most Eastern Europeans would understand what a schtetl was.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A sctetl-- a rabbi and a schtetl was your doctor.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was your preacher.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was your-- he was the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, he was not necessarily teaching you, or as a rabbi here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He was not necessarily staying in a schul giving sermons.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When you were sick, you didn't go to a doctor.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You went to the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "When you were-- when you were well, you didn't go anywhere else.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You went to the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He was-- he was the-- the person.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And whatever he said, you know, when he said it's Doomsday, it's Doomsday.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he said it's day, it's day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And when they killed this guy, I mean the whole town sort of-- I mean, we were about-- we were about like sheep without-- without a master.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We were just going.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And you've also got to understand that most of our capable men that were around living in that town were also gone.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So what you only had is wives, women, and the children, and-- and the younger people and some older men, who I guess the Russians felt are not capable to being our defenders.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
